the air; and 19
WHEREAS, In September 2023, President Biden issued 20
Executive Order 14108, "ensuring the people of East Palestine 21
are protected now and in the future." This Executive Order also 22
states, in pertinent part, that "available data show that no 23
contaminants of concern have been detected at levels of concern 24
in the air in the affected communities at sustained levels since 25
the evacuation order was lifted"; and 26
WHEREAS, The Executive Order also directed the Federal 27
Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to "oversee long-term 28
recovery efforts in the affected communities and conduct a 29
comprehensive assessment of unmet needs of the affected 30
communities in recovering from the derailment beyond the cleanup 31
work directed by EPA"; and 32
WHEREAS, Newly-obtained documents acquired through a 33
Freedom of Information Act request show that officials from FEMA 34
voiced concerns that the chemical spill and the plume of smoke 35
set off by the controlled burn could cause "cancer clusters"; 36
now therefore be it 37
RESOLVED, That we, the members of the House of 38
Representatives of the 136th General Assembly of the State of 39
Ohio, in adopting this resolution, urge Congress to establish a 40
special committee to investigate the East Palestine train 41
derailment and the United States Environmental Protection 42
Agency's response to it; and be it further 43
RESOLVED, That we, the members of the House of 44
Representatives of the 136th General Assembly of the State of 45
Ohio, in adopting this resolution, urge Congress to appoint 46
members of the Ohio Congressional delegation to the special 47
committee; and be it further 48
